<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1967-05-15T18:03:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1967-05-15T18:03:00-05:00" n="358" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d358">
                        <head>358. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss>
                            to the <gloss type="to">Mission of the European Office of the United
                                Nations</gloss><note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d358fn1">Source:
                                Department of State, Eyes Only Reels. Secret; Flash;
                                Limdis/Potatoes. Text received from the White House, and approved by
                                Roger Morris (<gloss target="#t_SS1">S/S</gloss>-<gloss target="#t_S1">S</gloss>).</note>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1967-05-15T19:03:00-04:00">May 15, 1967, 7:03 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline></opener>
                        <p>194633. Personal from the President for Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_RWM2">Roth</persName>. <persName corresp="#p_BFM1">Francis</persName> has just reported to me that we have a Kennedy
                            Round bargain. I want you to know what a first-rate job you, Mike and
                            your team have done, and how much I appreciate it. Congratulations. I
                            look forward to your report.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_RD3">
                                    <hi rend="strong">Rusk</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>